Microcystic adenoma of the pancreas--a case report. A 65-year-old female patient with microcystic adenoma of the pancreatic head is reported. Under suspicion of a malignant pancreatic tumour a kephalic duodenopancreatectomy (Kausch-Whipple) was performed. Diagnosis, therapy, prognosis and pathological anatomical aspects of benign microcystic adenoma are discussed.